ANC 3D recommends that the Board grant The Field School’s requested modifications and special exception. Modifications include: 
a. Construction of a new addition to be known as the Innovation Center;
b. Minor upgrades to the existing athletic field that will include new lighting and a
new/relocated scoreboard;
c. Reconfiguration of the existing basketball court and parking areas to the north of the
athletic field to create a practice field;
d. Reconfiguration of the School’s existing parking lot and bus parking zone;
   PO Box 40846, Palisades Station l Washington, DC 20016 l 3D@anc.dc.gov l www.anc3D.org
e. Increase to the student enrollment cap from 400 to 425; and
f. Increase to the FTE faculty/staff cap from 110 to 120.

ANC 3D also supports the requested special exception to allow the construction of three over- height retaining walls central to the campus.

ANC 2F supports enhancement to the Mid City Clean Team contract to support the following service enhancements: 
•	Twice annual mulching of street trees;
•	Planting of spillways constructed during the 14th Street DDOT streetscape project;
•	Demonstration project for decorative planting along one block of 14th street as a proof of concept;
•	Additional clean-up after the Pride Parade; and 
•	Extension of the service area on 14th Street to include the area between U Street and Florida Avenue.

